## üö® Common JSX/React Syntax Pitfalls

### Quote Nesting in JSX

**‚ùå NEVER DO THIS:**
```jsx
// Nested quotes in className - WILL BREAK
<div className="bg-[url('data:image/svg+xml,...')]"></div>
<div className="text-[color: 'red']"></div>
```

**‚úÖ DO THIS INSTEAD:**
```jsx
// Use inline styles for complex data URLs
<div 
  className="opacity-20"
  style={{
    backgroundImage: `url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg...")`
  }}
></div>

// Or use CSS variables
<div 
  className="pattern-bg"
  style={{ '--pattern-url': `url("data:image/svg+xml,...")` }}
></div>
```

### Data URLs and SVG Patterns

**When to use inline styles:**
- Data URLs with complex SVG content
- URLs containing quotes or special characters
- Dynamic background images
- Base64 encoded images

**When to use Tailwind classes:**
- Simple color values
- Standard gradients
- Static image paths (without quotes)
- Standard utility classes

**Best Practice:**
```jsx
// ‚úÖ GOOD: Inline style for data URL
<div 
  style={{
    backgroundImage: `url("data:image/svg+xml,${encodeURIComponent(svgString)}")`
  }}
></div>

// ‚úÖ GOOD: Tailwind for simple backgrounds
<div className="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-blue to-brand-orange"></div>

// ‚ùå BAD: Data URL in Tailwind arbitrary value
<div className="bg-[url('data:image/svg+xml,...')]"></div>
```

### JSX Attribute Syntax

**Common Mistakes to Avoid:**

1. **Nested Quotes:**
   - ‚ùå `className="text-[color: 'red']"`
   - ‚úÖ `className="text-red-500"` or `style={{ color: 'red' }}`

2. **Complex Expressions in className:**
   - ‚ùå `className={`bg-[url('${pattern}')]`}`
   - ‚úÖ `style={{ backgroundImage: `url("${pattern}")` }}`

3. **Unescaped Special Characters:**
   - ‚ùå `className="bg-[url('data:...')]"`
   - ‚úÖ Use `style` prop or CSS variables

4. **Template Literals in Tailwind Arbitrary Values:**
   - ‚ùå `className={`bg-[${color}]`}`
   - ‚úÖ `style={{ backgroundColor: color }}`

### Background Patterns

**Recommended Approach:**
```jsx
// Option 1: Inline style (best for data URLs)
<div 
  className="absolute inset-0 opacity-20"
  style={{
    backgroundImage: `url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg...")`
  }}
></div>

// Option 2: CSS variable (for reusable patterns)
<div 
  className="pattern-overlay"
  style={{ 
    '--pattern': `url("data:image/svg+xml,...")` 
  }}
></div>

// Option 3: External SVG file (best for complex patterns)
<div 
  className="absolute inset-0 opacity-20"
  style={{
    backgroundImage: 'url("/patterns/grid.svg")'
  }}
></div>
```

### Encoding Data URLs

**Always encode SVG data URLs properly:**
```jsx
// ‚úÖ GOOD: Properly encoded
const svgPattern = encodeURIComponent(`
  <svg width="60" height="60">
    <rect fill="#ffffff" opacity="0.05"/>
  </svg>
`);

<div style={{ backgroundImage: `url("data:image/svg+xml,${svgPattern}")` }}></div>

// ‚ùå BAD: Unencoded special characters
<div style={{ backgroundImage: 'url("data:image/svg+xml,<svg>...</svg>")' }}></div>
```

